1} M_\\odot$ is\nmatched in our model, and is related to significant change in halo gas density\naround this galaxy mass, which is a consequence of the lower cooling rates at\nhigher virial temperature. Wind and infall models overpredict the radio\nluminosities at small galaxy masses and have no particular steepening of the\nrun of the radio luminosities predicted at any galaxy mass. [...]\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 31 May 2019 10:52:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-07-10"}
